<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_ea2ff050-a87b-4234-be17-bb1349310540" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/></meta><sptc>7.2.6</sptc><title id="_3217c7f3-3278-49bc-8701-e3e17f9afbec">Installation of roofing sheets</title><archive-num>2019: 3.5.1.6</archive-num><subclause id="_47571886-4786-4743-8b66-a195cf6d5126" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_d68f3fee-fa6b-4bc4-abc3-d56982b63782">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Sheets must be—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_4b33e207-7112-4c11-9c5e-5855301723ac">laid wherever possible using complete lengths from the fascia to ridge; or</li><li id="_77c870cc-cbbd-4c76-a95b-c1aa132e8b1a">where a complete length cannot be laid—<ol><li>each run must be laid from bottom to top before moving on to the next run (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/642_0.6.0.xml#_0515f8a5-44e2-43eb-8ecb-548dabe1a273" id="_39d6b6b4-8965-4a5a-adc7-0d330f3ce581" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 7.2.6</xref>); and</li><li>the minimum end lap must be—<ol><li>for roof slopes above 15 degrees (1:4) – 150 mm; and</li><li>for roof slopes between 5–15 degrees (1:12-1:4) – 200 mm; and</li></ol></li></ol></li><li id="_6d3f6416-6d83-4346-8c45-efbe48130378">stop ended (i.e. each valley turned up 60 degrees) at the ridge line of each length.</li></ol></subclause><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/642_0.6.0.xml" id="_0515f8a5-44e2-43eb-8ecb-548dabe1a273"><num/><title id="_42f21ad0-0700-4c30-a833-de80c025c2c6"/></image-reference></clause>